		Comment <a href="#c_1714080710">11</a> by Sankate Sharma
		posted on 3/24/2014 at 8:15 AM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>Thanks Raymond, this is exactly what I was looking for.</p><p>For those like me who are new to Grunt, you do following</p><p>Create Gruntfile.js using the contents specified in the blog</p><p>1. npm init <br>2. sudo npm install grunt --save-dev<br>3. npm install<br>4. sudo npm install grunt-contrib-watch --save-dev<br>5. sudo npm install grunt-exec --save-dev</p><p>#1 will create a package.json for you, #2 - #5 will update package.json and add dev dependencies<br>  "devDependencies": {<br>    "grunt": "~0.4.4",<br>    "grunt-contrib-watch": "~0.6.1",<br>    "grunt-exec": "~0.4.5"<br>  }</p><p>Now you are good to go, just fire up grunt in your shell.</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		
